article.description: Jaylon Hall scored 17 points to lead Wright State to a 98-68 victory over Division II Ohio Valley on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Hall scores 17 points, Wright State beats Ohio Valley 98-68
article.linkText: Hall scores 17 points, Wright State beats Ohio Valley 98-68
article.story: DAYTON, Ohio -- Jaylon Hall scored 17 points to lead Wright State to a 98-68 victory over Division II Ohio Valley on Tuesday night. Hall was 7 of 11 from the floor. Loudon Love, Mark Hughes, and Grant Benzinger each added 16 points for Wright State (5-4), which has won five of its last six games. The Raiders shot 65 percent from the field and made 10 of 20 3-pointers, but missed 11 free throws. Luka Djordjevic and Dylan Harrison scored 12 points apiece for Ohio Valley. Christian Alley chipped in 11 points. Wright State built a double-digit lead early, but consecutive 3-pointers from Kavon Swoope and Harrison pulled Ohio Valley to 24-18 midway through the first half. The Raiders closed the first half on a 23-12 surge for a 47-30 halftime lead and cruised from there.
